One of Caesar's assassins was Tullius Cimber, and it has been supposed— 1 do not know on what grounds—that this man was his brother. Whether or no he is different from the person mentioned below, v. 107, it is not easy to say. Estre denies, Orelli and others affirm, that he is the same. There is not much to guide us.
